        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2751114256" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4921916903550875408">I read the eponymous short story. <br/><br/>I read this story. Then I read it again. Then again. My heart felt the weight of being human. I have been like the narrator, operating in a world I organize with mathematical precision, tamping down grief with logic and staving off fear. I have been like Sonny, speaking and holding to the hope that someone will hear and share the experience of life. I live for moments when I read words crafted on a page that leave me staring out the window, sitting still, and ca</span>
  <span id="freeText4921916903550875408" style="display:none">I read the eponymous short story. <br /><br />I read this story. Then I read it again. Then again. My heart felt the weight of being human. I have been like the narrator, operating in a world I organize with mathematical precision, tamping down grief with logic and staving off fear. I have been like Sonny, speaking and holding to the hope that someone will hear and share the experience of life. I live for moments when I read words crafted on a page that leave me staring out the window, sitting still, and catching my breath. It is a personal, private response, but it is also why I have pursued a profession in education, literature, and libraries. It would be an honor to share this work with students, hoping they, too might find the freedom of listening. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="4921916903550875408" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


